[SN]TITLE[SN]
Archbishop speaks of 'resurrection moments' in Easter message

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
The Archbishop of Wales has used his Easter message to urge Christians to "be alert to the presence of God".

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Dr Barry Morgan said "resurrection moments" happen "when we see the power of God at work".
He said the "power of God" is present when we see "unexpected acts of kindness from strangers, forgiveness, generosity and sacrifice".
The archbishop held a service at Llandaff Cathedral, Cardiff, on Easter Sunday.
